##Four days and four nights, Hubei Drivers high-speed drifting record

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

By Chen Yihan

Editor | 林鹏

On the afternoon of the Lantern Festival, Xiao Hongbing, a 50-year-old truck driver, finally took his first hot bath in more than 20 days in a fully equipped room in Hanzhong's North Service district.

Xiao Hongbing, a native of Tianmen in Hubei Province, hardly left the EOM3B350 during the Spring Festival. A temporary business deal delayed his planned return home before New Year's Eve, and an extended epidemic left him stranded in Hubei Province in early January.

The Red Jianghuai truck with the striking word "Hubei" was originally his "brother" , he often praised it, "brother, the hardest thing is you, drag how much, run how far also don't make a sound" . This Spring Festival, "brother" in addition to help him make money, but also became a barometer of the progress of the epidemic. At first, the noodle shop owner believed that he sold him a bowl of Sichuan bashful noodles on New Year's Eve; later, he went to buy shoes, 59 dollars of shoes, do not wait for him to ask, "30 dollars to sell you" , the requirement is: Pay Code Open, stand two or three meters back, the boss again sweep code; Later, when the villagers started calling the police, he was repeatedly stopped and even driven up a cliff in the mountains.

At its worst, when everyone was telling him, go back to where you came from, he held his phone in his hand and had no idea where to navigate to, as if on a high-speed call to go home. The 110 people in their hometown of Tianmen, Hubei Province, said the roads were closed until the outbreak was over. He understood the policy, did not want to give trouble to others, had to drive aimlessly.

Now he's more than 900 kilometers from home, waiting for the outbreak to end. His greatest wish was to be back home in the spring ploughing season, driving the red JAC, carrying seeds, fertilizer, and last season's harvest of wheat and rape.

Here's what Xiao Hongbing said:

New Year's Eve for the homeless

Late last year, December 27th, 28th, I left home. First in the home 300-400 kilometers from the place to pull goods, January 7 from Jingzhou, Hubei, has gone to Yiwu, Guiyang, Xiangtan, Shenzhen and other places, to Fuzhou on the twenty-seven wax month. Originally, I planned to send the goods to Fuzhou to go home for the Spring Festival. Before I left, I had an urgent job to deliver a batch of food festival exhibits. Near Nianguan, there were fewer cars running on the road. The owner said he would give me more money to bring the goods to Sichuan.

It was $2,000 for this one, and he raised it by another $200. I thought we were GONNA make more money with the sports car, so I agreed. My son is going to take the junior high exam this year, and he needs money. I called my wife and told her I couldn't go home for Spring Festival.

I bought this used Van last October. At first, I didn't think of long distance, but I took orders within 100 or 200 kilometers and made a round trip that day. Ran For more than a month, found that this place is limited supply of goods, sometimes stay a few days can not pull live. But then I thought about it, you know, long distance. At first, my wife and I ran together. There was little room in the car. Only one person could lie in the back seat. The other person had to sleep in the passenger seat. Every day, and it was bumpy. Ran for a month, see her really hard, let her follow.

On this trip to Sichuan, the seller sent me three things -- two bottles of red bull, a pair of gloves, and 20 or 30 disposable masks. "You need it, " he said, and I thought, "I'm sure you need it, even if you're burning the midnight oil and red bull, but I don't know how you're going to use it. I didn't know anything about the outbreak, and I didn't ask any questions.

I set out from Fuzhou, through Jiangxi and Hunan to Sichuan. There were very few cars on the way. I thought about the New Year. It was normal that there were few cars. I didn't think about anything else. It wasn't until New Year's Eve afternoon in Kaijiang County, Sichuan Province, that I realized something was wrong as I prepared to pay the toll at the highway exit. There was a checkpoint sixty meters ahead of the toll window, and a lot of policemen in blue, hooded suits were pointing at my car.

I hadn't been wearing a mask before, and when I got to the checkpoint, I saw that everyone was wearing one, so I grabbed one and put it on. The police take my temperature, sterilize me, get my ID card and registration information. When I asked them what was going on, they said that the COVID-19 epidemic was now spreading, that the whole country was preventing and controlling it, and that the source was our Hubei Province, I just found out about this situation.

I kept all the high-speed receipts for this period to prove that I had not been to Hubei recently and that my temperature was normal, 36.3 °c, and they let me go, reminding me to leave as soon as possible after unloading.

When unloading the cargo, one after another came to seven or eight civilians, gathered in front of the car thirty meters. A short while later, two policemen came, I said the situation again, bills and papers out again, this is fine.

After unloading, I went to a noodle shop. Boss Niang said: "Just the Police Stop Your car? " I think, how to spread so fast? It makes me look like a plague. Fortunately, she is very good, know I did not return to Hubei for half a month, said: "I am not afraid, this side I sell you to eat. " I ate a bowl of the most common Sichuan bashful noodles, even if it is a New Year's Eve dinner.

Later, when I went shopping, they were a little wary of my accent. They said they trust me, but they were still a little scared to see Hubei People. They told me to stand back.

I saw a pair of shoes at the original price of 59 dollars, thought to bargain, they simply said, 30 dollars to sell to you. I thought I'd give it a try, but then I thought I'd let it go without causing them any trouble. When I paid, they asked me to open the code, stand two or three meters back, and they scanned the code.

Back in the car, I wanted to take a break. Two men in their 50s pushed their tricycles toward me and stopped my car one after the other. One guy's taking pictures with his phone, the other one's on the phone. Then they came over and said, "we've called the police, you'd better go. " I knew the general situation and understood their feelings, so I drove away.

I think I'm gonNA take the highway. Before, the police told me not to stop after unloading the cargo: "You are safe with us, but some people may be impatient when we go elsewhere. " They told me to take the highway as far as possible, and no people set up checkpoints, it's safer.

I called home before I got on the highway. It was almost 7 o'clock, and my wife, kids and parents were all together, just in time for dinner. According to our customs, no matter whether the family has money or not, it is 10 dishes. My father went to battle himself, and though he knew I wouldn't be able to return, he cooked several dishes that I loved, such as braised fish in vinegar, pig's feet and peanuts. Wife says you don't eat at home, something's always missing. I said it's fine. I'm making money for the family.

30,40 minutes on the phone, and I didn't tell them what I just went through. My parents are in their 70s, their blood pressure's high, their heart's not great, and I don't want to upset them. With his wife, children are also good said, I talked to the child for a while, let him obey, encourage him to do better grades, if the test well, we can save some entrance fees.

Xiao Hongbing and his red Jianghuai. (photo: Sohu Video)

I want to cry. I don't have time to cry

I'm on the highway, and I can't go home. From Sichuan to Hubei has more than 1000 kilometers, if the empty car to go back, the expenditure to more than 2000 yuan, equivalent to the money earned on a single run on the road, too not worthwhile. The family also said, as far as possible to choose a little closer to home list, after the goods pull, go home near a trip. I searched the truck gang for a long time, and found one, which was sent to Ankang.

I was more than 400 kilometers from the city proper, and Chenggu County wasn't too far from Ankang. I wouldn't normally take a job like this, but I wanted to go home, so I took it. I got through to the platform, paid a $100 deposit, and headed to Chenggu County. 80 or 90 kilometers later, they found out I was from Hubei and said No.

It was around 12 o'clock at night and I had to park in a service area near Jiangyou in Sichuan Province. It's a big service area. No one can see one, just this one car. No one had turned me away that night, but I hadn't showered in days, I was Itchy, and I woke up after less than three hours. At dawn, I set off, ready to get off the highway to find a cheap motel, open an hour room to take a shower, change clothes.

As a result, roadblocks were set up everywhere, and no one was allowed to get off the expressway. Signs were posted at toll booths that read "epidemic prevention and control, no entry and exit" . I was a little flustered, but I was told there was an announcement, and I was trying to get back to where I came from.

It was bad, it was understandable, it was acceptable, and I was back on the highway. Unexpectedly, this time I floated on the road for four days and nights.

Once, I pulled into a parking area for a quick bite of instant noodles and was whisked away by a young worker. We fought all the time. I said, can I rest here for a while? I haven't slept all night. I'm tired from driving. I haven't been back for half a month, the police have investigated, the epidemic prevention personnel have also checked, there are no problems, why can't we stop? He said, "you just can't stop here. ". Next thing I know, he's banging on my door. I had no choice but to keep going. However, at that time I was a little angry, I have to give me a reason to leave, I do not have evidence in Hubei, the police did not chase me away, you chase me away?

I wanted to go home. The destination had changed from Chenggu County to Jingzhou. The navigation went wrong, and it led to a place called Ningqiang County, which changed from a highway to a national highway. At one o'clock at night, I got to the entrance of the national highway. I was stopped by a crossbar. A piece of paper hung on the crossbar said, "No non-town personnel or vehicles are allowed to enter. " I had to change the country road.

I was about to enter the provincial road when I was stopped by some tables. There was a shed nearby, and someone was on duty. Seeing that I was a Hubei License Plate, he pointed at me and said, "hurry up, or I'll call the police. " After passing through a tunnel, he was able to reach my destination in no time, but instead of letting me go, he pointed me to an old road, follow the cliff up the hill.

It's a really dangerous part of the trail. My car is two meters wide, and the road is only about two meters wide. From time to time will encounter a mass of fog, turn on the headlights can only see three or four meters.

It was so quiet that I didn't see any cars. My car doesn't have a radio, my phone is a 400-yuan domestic brand, I can't even say the brand name, it doesn't even have a brand name, in order to save traffic, I didn't download any songs. So absentmindedly open, do not know is illusory or reality. Don't joke about it. To stay awake, I pinch my thighs, pull my hair, and at the worst of times, smack my mouth. I can't think of anything. I'm afraid I'll fall off a cliff.

Early in the morning, my father sent a wechat with a smile, then I want to cry, but no time to cry.

Finally, I made it to the provincial road. At 6 am, I arrived in Hanzhong, Shaanxi Province. After walking this far, I was a little reluctant to go to the platform to find a suitable list, also from Chenggu County, to transport rice to Shiyan.

I told the platform to tell the shipper that I was from Hubei. They said it was fine. They could pull any car anywhere. There were a few stops along the way, but it was too early and no one showed up for work, so I got there without a hitch. By the time I pulled up to the factory, people were calling the police again. I asked the police, Hubei can still go back? Sounds like they don't know what's going on when I go back to the meeting.

In Sichuan, I did not feel angry or aggrieved, the epidemic so serious, what the country's regulatory policy, we also understand. And then I couldn't stop, I couldn't walk, and that was a little sad. I can't stop on the highway. I can't keep running. I haven't slept in days and nights, and I haven't eaten much, and I haven't had any boiling blisters on my instant noodles. I'm so hungry, I just chew them dry. I didn't know where to navigate. I didn't know where to go.

I just drove around aimlessly, and then I thought, try to stay close to Hubei.

"and good people. "

In fact, I've come up with a lot of ideas along the way.

12122 high-speed rescue call, the other side said to be able to go home or home, now the epidemic is more serious. I also called the 110 Tianmen, they said that Hubei Road are closed, not back, can we ask the local 110 for help, and then come back when the epidemic lifted? I guess the cops told me to go back as soon as I could, and they were in a bind, so they didn't call back.

I had a navigation problem, and I got dizzy and started driving in the opposite direction. At noon on the 29th, near Hanzhong, I was so sleepy that I pulled into the emergency driveway and tried to get some sleep. I had slept in the emergency lane before, and had been told by the police, but I couldn't stand it any longer and fell asleep as soon as I lay down.

At 3 p.m. , I was awakened by the sound of the police banging on the window. They saw that I was falling apart and said, "come with us. We'll take you somewhere to rest. "

I followed a squad car to a tollbooth on the highway north of Mian County. I was nervous on the way. It was illegal parking. I didn't know what they were going to do. When I got out of the car, the attendant brought me some buns, some oranges, and some milk. I figured it was their own work meal, because the BUN's wrapper had been torn.

When they brought me the food, my tears came right down. The last couple of days have been a lot of pushing, and I really didn't think there were any good guys like that. Then they took me to the North Hanzhong service area, where they said no one would turn me away and I could stay there.

Photo of Xiao Hongbing and Hanzhong police

When I got to the service area, I had a long sleep, from afternoon to 10 o'clock the next day. When I woke up, I called home. I haven't talked to them since New Year's Eve. The incoming calls were not answered, first, the cell phone signal is bad, afraid of a navigation interrupt it is difficult to reconnect, and second, do not want to tell them I was so embarrassed.

As soon as the call went through, my mother cried. I was the only child they had, and the first thing she said was, I'm glad to be alive. The other day, they were afraid something would happen to me, but at least the phone was still on, and they knew it was still charged, which means the engine was still on, so I should still be alive. I told them that the service area leader is very good, specially arranged people, give me daily temperature, disinfection, send food. The head of the traffic police also came to visit and took a condolence gift.

They said, do not come back, home situation is quite grim, closed down the community.

I spent the next few days in the service area. At first there is a quarantine period, I basically do not get off the car during the day, to the evening, to ensure that no one around, quickly run out of the car, make some instant noodles, go to the toilet. I try not to bother the people in the service area, just in case they kick me out.

There was a gas station about 100 meters away, and the drivers used to look sideways, and one of the Shijiazhuang drivers took a picture of my car. Then I saw a car coming at me, and I was scared.

We drive a van. We're always on the road, alone. Having said that, I have never encountered such a situation, before every two or three days can talk to the owner, now the only person I can see is the food delivery director Wang. I look forward to his coming every day, say a word, two words.

Every other day, I skype with my family. Cell phones do not dare to use too long, to start the car can be charged, fuel, I only see more than 10 minutes a day, to see friends circle, to see the family sent the news of the Tianmen epidemic. The rest of the time is just staring into space, or thinking about what I've learned. Five or six years ago I planted vegetables and invested in a 110 acre vegetable farm. My savings and money borrowed from relatives and friends in previous years added up to more than $1 million, which was later completely wiped out. Because it was a shakeout in the farming industry, and there was more supply than demand. But I still like this, before saving some related forums in the mobile browser bookmarks, these days, I will occasionally turn over to see, think if I do, how can play strengths.

To save gas, I barely turn on the air conditioner. Fine by day, sleeping at night, often waking up in the middle of the night. That's when I turn on the air conditioner, blow on the heater for an hour, and then turn it off.

Every once in a while, I'd get out of my car and look at the Sun. I'd park in the shade. It was dark all day. There's not much to see here, either. It's bare. Look at the Sun. It feels good.

"Wait till spring, then take my car for a run. "

About five or six days ago, the service area was closed. After two days, no one came to deliver the food. I know, they live a little far away from home, back and forth is not convenient, just eat the car store food bar.

Before the head of the traffic police sent a box of instant noodles, I did not want to move, thought after returning to Hubei, to the media here to help me, then, this box of noodles as a primitive basis. After half an hour of hesitation, I unpacked the box. I took a picture of it before I opened it.

On February 7th, with only three boxes of instant noodles, three apples and six small cartons of milk left, I panicked. I used to be a soldier in Shaanxi, and I got to know a lot of friends, so I called a friend in Xi'an to see if he could help. He's a registered microblogger, and I commissioned him to post a cry for help.

On Feb. 7, Xiao Hongbing took a picture of what was left of the food and commissioned a friend to ask for help online. Photo courtesy of the respondents

About an hour later, the first call came from a man in Xi'an. He wanted to drive me some food, but it turned out to be 200,300 kilometers away, and it was hard to get back. Then I got about 20 more calls, all from well meaning strangers, but the nearest one was seventy miles away and I couldn't get to it. But I appreciate the encouragement.

At that time, I thought to myself, eat a box of instant noodles a day, and can last three days, plus apples, five days is no problem, and six small boxes of milk, should be able to last three days.

February 8th, the Lantern Festival, the service area staff came. They gave me a room, like a standard hotel room, with two beds, air conditioning, TV, kettle, and a separate bathroom. Before, you could stay here for free until you came home, Wang said. They served red bean filling Yuanxiao, eating very sweet. I took a bath in the evening, more than 20 days, the first time to take a hot bath, really comfortable.

Now I am more than 900 kilometers away from the Heaven Gate. Tianmen is a big agricultural city. After the 15th day of the first lunar month in the past, it has started to transport materials for spring cultivation. When spring comes and people start to sow, there is a little sense of hope. Well, you live with hope.

By May Day, the wheat and rape planted before the harvest, but also transplant rice seedlings. We call this period "double grab" , grab the harvest, grab planting, is the most need for the truck. I want the outbreak to be over as soon as possible, before the "double grab" , and then get in my car and run.

My car is a red JAC. This half year we have cultivated feelings, I often say to it: "Brother, the most difficult is you, drag how much, run how far also do not say. " Recently, it can finally rest.
